cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.CY 

The paper focuses on the development of information flow analyses to support resilient design and active detection of adversaries in cyber physical systems (CPS), specifically control systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis, design, and control of dynamical systems. 

The paper also discusses security issues in CPS, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

Furthermore, the paper proposes the use of information flow analysis, which is a well-established set of methods developed in software security, indicating that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). 

The paper also discusses the use of optimal detection techniques and active detection mechanisms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well as cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical implications of computing.
